cause Linda is great — not because the system is great. If Linda leaves, the location regresses. You know this because it happened in Phoenix last year."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"You have a billing director at HQ. She's drowning. She's overseeing eleven separate workflows that should be one workflow."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Payroll has grown 40% in two years. Collections growth hasn't kept pace."}],["$","p",null,{"children":["$","em",null,{"children":"You don't need more people. You need a different operating model."}]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-ledger fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-row","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pn","children":"01"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"ptitle","children":"Eleven locations, eleven workflows."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pdesc","children":"Standardization decays as you scale. What was once \"how we do things\" becomes \"how each office does things.\" Reporting gaps widen. Quality varies by site."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-row","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pn","children":"02"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"ptitle","children":"Performance depends on people, not systems."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pdesc","children":"Your best office is best because of a person. When that person leaves, the location moves. That's not a business — that's a craft shop."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-row","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pn","children":"03"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"ptitle","children":"Payroll is outpacing collections."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pdesc","children":"You added three billers, two MAs, and a coordinator last year. Collections grew 6%. Operational margin shrank. The math is heading the wrong direction."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-row","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pn","children":"04"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"ptitle","children":"Reporting tells you what, not why."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pdesc","children":"AR is at 41 days. Houston is at 58. You see it on the dashboard. You don't see why. Or who. Or what to do about it."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-row","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pn","children":"05"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"ptitle","children":"Standardization is a project nobody finishes."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pdesc","children":"Every quarter someone writes a new SOP doc. Three offices adopt it. Two don't. Six adopt the parts they like. By next quarter, it's stale."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-row","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pn","children":"06"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"ptitle","children":"Talent acquisition is consuming leadership time."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pdesc","children":"Your billing director is interviewing instead of optimizing. Your COO is recruiting instead of strategizing. You're solving last quarter's hiring problem while next quarter's bottleneck builds."}]]}]]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"block warm","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"What's actually happening behind the scenes"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display","children":["You don't have an execution problem. ",["$","em",null,{"children":"You have an operating model problem."}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"monologue fade-in","style":{"maxWidth":820},"children":[["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--sans)","fontSize":17,"lineHeight":"1.65","color":"var(--ink-mute)"},"children":"Most multi-location groups grow the same way: replicate the original office, hire a manager, hope it works. It scales until it doesn't — usually somewhere between 5 and 12 locations, where the cost of inconsistency starts to outweigh the cost of the next hire."}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--sans)","fontSize":17,"lin